{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idee8011ad-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s1335"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1335"},"text":"§ 1335.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Small-farm exemption; small-farm base acreage; election; acreage allotment; land-use provisions; price support; wheat marketing certificates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of this subpart, no farm marketing quota for any crop of wheat shall be applicable to any farm with a farm acreage allotment of less than fifteen acres if the acreage of such crop of wheat does not exceed the small-farm base acreage determined for the farm, unless the operator elects in writing on a form and within the time prescribed by the Secretary to be subject to the farm acreage allotment and marketing quota. The small-farm base acreage for a farm shall be the smaller of (A) the average acreage of the crop of wheat planted for harvest in the three years 1959, 1960, and 1961, or such later three-year period, excluding 1963, determined by the Secretary to be representative, with adjustments for abnormal weather conditions, established crop-rotation practices on the farm, and such other factors as the Secretary determines should be considered for the purpose of establishing a fair and equitable small-farm base acreage, or (B) fifteen acres. The acreage allotment for any farm shall be the larger of (1) the small-farm base acreage determined as provided above on the basis of the three-year period 1959–1961, reduced by the same percentage by which the national acreage allotment for the crop is reduced below fifty-five million acres, or (2) the acreage allotment determined without regard to (1) above. If the operator of any such farm fails to make such election with respect to any crop of wheat, (i) for the purposes of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1340"},"text":"section 1340 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the farm acreage allotment for such crop of wheat shall be deemed to be the larger of (A) the small-farm base acreage or (B) the acreage allotment for the farm, (ii) the land-use provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1339"},"text":"section 1339 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be inapplicable to the farm, (iii) such crop of wheat shall not be eligible for price support, and (iv) wheat marketing certificates applicable to such crop shall not be issued with respect to the farm. The additional acreage required to provide acreage allotments for farms based upon small-farm base acreages under this section shall be in addition to National, State, and county acreage allotments. This section shall not be applicable to the crops planted for harvest in 1967 and subsequent years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idee8011ae-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-02-16/ch30"},"text":"Feb. 16, 1938, ch. 30","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 335, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/54"},"text":"52 Stat. 54","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-07-26/ch379"},"text":"July 26, 1939, ch. 379","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1126"},"text":"53 Stat. 1126","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-06-06/ch237"},"text":"June 6, 1940, ch. 237","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/232"},"text":"54 Stat. 232","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-07-03/ch827"},"text":"July 3, 1948, ch. 827","children":[],"tail":", title II, §§ 204(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/1256"},"text":"62 Stat. 1256","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-28/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1954, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 309, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/903"},"text":"68 Stat. 903","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/203/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–203, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1957-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1957","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/71/477"},"text":"71 Stat. 477","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/128/tI/s122/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–128, title I, § 122(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/297"},"text":"75 Stat. 297","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/703/tIII/s315"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–703, title III, § 315","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-09-27"},"text":"Sept. 27, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/621"},"text":"76 Stat. 621","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/321/tV/s501/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–321, title V, § 501(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-11-03"},"text":"Nov. 3, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/1201"},"text":"79 Stat. 1201","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/198/tIII/s305"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–198, title III, § 305","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1380"},"text":"99 Stat. 1380","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idee8011af-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idee8011b0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3